ing her of immorality<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=1&verse=19'>Mat 1:19</a> <br/> - Zacchaeus, in the administration of his wealth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=19&verse=8'>Luk 19:8</a> <br/> - Nathanael, in whom was no guile<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=1&verse=47'>Joh 1:47</a> <br/> - Joseph, a counselor<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=23&verse=51'>Luk 23:51</a> <br/> - Peter, when offered money by Simon Magus<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=8&verse=23'>Act 8:23</a> <br/> - Paul and Barnabas, when the people of Lystra desired to deify them<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=14&verse=15'>Act 14:15</a> "}]}